See `.claude/linum-govern/docs/system/README.md` for the governance workflow.
<!-- END linum-govern -->

## Stack-Specific Rules

**Framework**: Next.js 16.2.6 (App Router, breaking changes — check `node_modules/next/dist/docs/`)
**Language**: TypeScript 5 (strict mode)
**Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4
**Testing**: Playwright E2E
**Package manager**: bun
**i18n**: next-intl (en, pt-BR)

## Code Style

- Functions: 4–20 lines. Split if longer.
- Files: under 500 lines. Split by responsibility.
- SRP: one thing per function, one responsibility per module.
- Names: specific, unique. Avoid `data`, `handler`, `Manager`.
- Types: explicit. No `any`. Strict mode enforced.
- No duplication. Extract shared logic.
- Early returns over nested ifs. Max 2 indentation levels.
- Comments: WHY not WHAT. Reference issue/commit if context-dependent.

## Components & i18n

- **Components**: one per file, PascalCase naming, explicit Props interface
- **i18n**: all user-facing strings in `messages/{locale}.json`, never hardcoded
- **Hooks**: `use*` prefix, exported from component files
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS classes only, no inline styles

## Testing

- **Framework**: Playwright (E2E only)
- **Run**: `bun run test:e2e`
- **Location**: `tests/{visual,functional}/{feature}.spec.ts`
- **Rule**: every feature gets an E2E test; every bug gets a regression test

## Validation

Before commit:

```bash
bun run lint      # ESLint check
tsc --noEmit      # TypeScript check
bun run build     # Next.js build
bun run test:e2e  # Playwright E2E
```

All must pass. No exceptions.
